title: Violent Crimes and Property Crimes Committed per 100,000 persons, by Cities over 100,000 persons, USA
name: Violent Crimes and Property Crimes Committed per 100,000 persons, by Cities over 100,000 persons, USA
description: Information was compiled by the U.S. Department of Justice for the year 2005. It is the most current information that the Dept. of Justice maintains. Number of Crimes were measured in a rate per 100,000 persons. Please note that the shapefile to which I joined this information omitted both Indianapolis, IN and Nashville, TN - both of which were included on the original Justice Department data. The shapefile was quite complete in all other regards. Data Source: Bureau of Justice Statistics; U.S. Department of Justicehttp://bjsdata.ojp.usdoj.gov/dataonline/Search/Crime/State/RunCrimeOneYearofData.cfm
